505
00:30:50.022 --> 00:30:53.062
Now I'd like to also highlight the case of another patient.

506
00:30:53.122 --> 00:30:56.802
This is a patient with a primary refractory diffuse large B-cell

507
00:30:56.822 --> 00:30:59.722
lymphoma, fifth relapse of his disease.

508
00:30:59.762 --> 00:31:03.402
In this particular patient, CAR T-cell manufacturing had failed because he was so

509
00:31:03.422 --> 00:31:04.162
lymphopenic.

510
00:31:05.062 --> 00:31:05.262
And

511
00:31:07.062 --> 00:31:10.302
basically, we gave him the cells. He goes into complete remission.

512
00:31:10.322 --> 00:31:14.282
He's 18 months out. He's still in CR, and he had mediastinal disease that

513
00:31:14.302 --> 00:31:15.502
you can see disappeared.

514
00:31:16.362 --> 00:31:20.242
But the reason I want to highlight this is that the question always is asked

515
00:31:20.252 --> 00:31:24.121
around CAR NK cells is that do they proliferate and do they persist?

516
00:31:24.142 --> 00:31:27.182
And I think this example really shows that they do.

517
00:31:27.742 --> 00:31:31.722
So using HLA antibodies directed against the

518
00:31:31.882 --> 00:31:35.672
HLA mismatch between the donor NK cells and the recipient,

519
00:31:36.162 --> 00:31:38.052
we could follow expansion of the

520
00:31:39.162 --> 00:31:42.822
